    "keyPoints": "- Privacy policy must disclose categories of PI collected, purposes, third parties, and consumer rights; updated at least every 12 months (s 1798.130)\n- Notice must be provided at or before the point of collection (s 1798.100)\n- Service providers require written contracts prohibiting sale/sharing and restricting PI use to the direct business relationship (s 1798.140(ag))\n- Contractors (CPRA addition) have the same restrictions as service providers plus must allow compliance audits and provide contractual certification (s 1798.140(j))\n- Data minimization: collection and use must be reasonably necessary and proportionate to disclosed purposes\n- Businesses must respond to verifiable consumer requests within 45 days (extendable to 90)\n- A \"Do Not Sell or Share My Personal Information\" link is required on the homepage (s 1798.135)"
