    "keyPoints": "- Six rights total: three from the original CCPA (know, delete, opt-out, non-discrimination) and two added by CPRA (correct, limit sensitive PI use)\n- Businesses must respond to verifiable consumer requests within 45 days, extendable to 90 days\n- Right to know covers the preceding 12 months (CPRA extends beyond 12 months for PI collected on or after January 1, 2022)\n- Opt-out now covers both \"sale\" and \"sharing\" for cross-context behavioral advertising\n- Minors under 16 require opt-in for sale/sharing; under 13 requires parent/guardian authorization\n- Financial incentive programs are permitted under the non-discrimination right if reasonably related to PI value and consumer opts in"
