    "keyPoints": "- Eight distinct rights codified in Articles 15-22\n- Article 12 establishes the overarching framework: responses must be concise, transparent, intelligible, in plain language, and free of charge\n- Standard response deadline: one month from receipt of request, extendable by two additional months for complex or numerous requests (Article 12(3))\n- Controllers must verify the identity of the requester but cannot use this as an excuse to delay or refuse\n- Rights are not absolute -- Article 23 permits member state restrictions for national security, defense, public security, crime prevention, and other defined purposes\n- Failure to facilitate rights is one of the most commonly enforced GDPR violations"
